Notes We first define expressed genes in the cancer clone A or B cells (sender) and fibroblast cells (receiver). Genes are considered to be expressed within one cell type if their log2-transformed mean TPM (transcript per kilobase million) values are greater than 4, following the same criterion as in the NicheNet tutorial. The mean TPM value for each cell type is calculated based on the cell-type-specific gene expression of spots with the corresponding proportion greater than 0.05 within the focused spots.

lr_network <- readRDS("./realdata/LR_analysis/lr_network_human_21122021.rds")

ligand_target_matrix <-  readRDS("./realdata/LR_analysis/ligand_target_matrix_nsga2r_final.rds")

Notes: Filtering Expressed Genes

keep_genes <- rownames(stged$F_list$Fibroblasts)

keep_spots_clonea <- stged$beta[,"Cancer clone A"] > 0.05
keep_spots_cloneb <- stged$beta[,"Cancer clone B" ] > 0.05
keep_spots_fibro <- stged$beta[,"Fibroblasts"] > 0.05

# Identify expressed genes for T cells, macrophages, and malignant cells
expressed_genes_clonea <- keep_genes[log2(rowMeans(stged$F_list[["Cancer clone A"]][,keep_spots_clonea, 
                                                                                     drop = FALSE] * 1e6) + 1) >= 4]

expressed_genes_cloneb<- keep_genes[log2(rowMeans(stged$F_list[["Cancer clone B"]][,keep_spots_cloneb, drop = FALSE] * 1e6) + 1) >= 4]

expressed_genes_fibro<- keep_genes[log2(rowMeans(stged$F_list[["Fibroblasts"]][,keep_spots_fibro, drop = FALSE] * 1e6) + 1) >= 4]

Notes:The gene set of interest comprises the identified potential interaction-changed genes, encompassing both significantly positively correlated genes and significantly negatively correlated genes.

geneset_ctHVG_clonea <- intersect(convert_alias_to_symbols(toupper(clonea), "human", verbose = FALSE), colnames(ligand_target_matrix))

geneset_ctHVG_cloneb <- intersect(convert_alias_to_symbols(toupper(cloneb), "human", verbose = FALSE), colnames(ligand_target_matrix))

Notes:

test_genes <- rownames(stged$F_list$Fibroblasts)[rowSums(stged$F_list$Fibroblasts) != 0]

background_expressed_genes <- intersect(convert_alias_to_symbols(toupper(test_genes), "human", verbose = FALSE), rownames(ligand_target_matrix))

Notes:The potential ligands are defined as ligands expressed in at least one immune cell type and for which at least one putative receptor is expressed in malignant cells.

# Identify ligands and receptors from the ligand-receptor network
ligands <- lr_network %>% pull(from) %>% unique()

expressed_ligands_clonea <- intersect(ligands, expressed_genes_clonea)
expressed_ligands_cloneb <- intersect(ligands, expressed_genes_cloneb)

receptors <- lr_network %>% pull(to) %>% unique()
expressed_receptors <- intersect(receptors, expressed_genes_fibro)

# Identify potential ligands interacting with receptors
potential_ligands_clonea <- lr_network %>% filter(from %in% expressed_ligands_clonea & to %in% expressed_receptors) %>% pull(from) %>% unique()

potential_ligands_cloneb <- lr_network %>% filter(from %in% expressed_ligands_cloneb & to %in% expressed_receptors) %>% pull(from) %>% unique()

Notes:We then perform NicheNets ligand activity analysis.

# Predict ligand activities for cancer clone a
ligand_activities_clonea <- predict_ligand_activities(
  geneset = geneset_ctHVG_clonea, 
  background_expressed_genes = background_expressed_genes, 
  ligand_target_matrix = ligand_target_matrix, 
  potential_ligands = potential_ligands_clonea
)

best_upstream_ligands_clonea <- ligand_activities_clonea %>% arrange(-aupr_corrected) %>% pull(test_ligand)

# Predict ligand activities forcancer clone b
ligand_activities_cloneb <- predict_ligand_activities(
  geneset = geneset_ctHVG_cloneb, 
  background_expressed_genes = background_expressed_genes, 
  ligand_target_matrix = ligand_target_matrix, 
  potential_ligands = potential_ligands_cloneb
)

best_upstream_ligands_cloneb <- ligand_activities_cloneb %>% arrange(-aupr_corrected) %>% pull(test_ligand)

Notes:Assign specific ligands to cell types based on expression levels

clonea_specific_ligands <- intersect(best_upstream_ligands_clonea, expressed_ligands_clonea)

cloneb_specific_ligands <- intersect(best_upstream_ligands_cloneb, expressed_ligands_cloneb)

Notes: When inferring target genes of the ligands, we consider the top 100 targets of at least one ligand according to the prior model.

active_ligand_target_links_df_clonea <- best_upstream_ligands_clonea %>% 
  lapply(get_weighted_ligand_target_links, geneset = geneset_ctHVG_clonea, ligand_target_matrix = ligand_target_matrix, n = 100) %>% 
  bind_rows()

active_ligand_target_links_df_cloneb <- best_upstream_ligands_cloneb %>% 
  lapply(get_weighted_ligand_target_links, geneset = geneset_ctHVG_cloneb, ligand_target_matrix = ligand_target_matrix, n = 100) %>% 
  bind_rows()
